protectionFromHarassment.harassmentPolicy:
MentorED follows best practices to keep user data safe and secure. No personal data is shared among collaborators and only with the explicit consent of all participating individuals, a collaboration flow can be triggered. Registrations of users are done in a regulated manner, for example, there is a help page for reporting any issue. MentorED software implements principles of minimalism, consent, transparency of data collection, and other best practices.

Some of the steps taken to ensure the safety of users are:
1. Profile controls to modify and manage data stored against the user profile;
2. Two-Factor Authentication (OTP based);
3. Users join a Group by accepting an invite (no one can add a user to a group without their consent);
4. Users can exit discussion areas at any time;
5. Users agree to the terms and conditions. 

Processes that address the safety and security of underage users :
6. Sessions are recorded for ensuring security; 
7. A support page to raise concerns; 
8. No PII data is shared within the users ;
9. No communication is possible between the users outside the session;

MentorED has microservices for reporting. But, typically adopters can extend this to cater to the specific needs of the users and processes within their context.
